  "source_notes": "Sy Scholfield quotes from Baron Franz von Zach's account published in May 1802, \"On March 31 we got a letter from our esteemed friend Dr. Olbers from Bremen ... telling us that he had been so lucky as to discover on March 28 a moving star in the northern wing of Virgo ... His first thought was that this might be a variable star ... He immediately compared the stranger to 20 Virgo and continued his observations from 8:45 to 11 o'clock ... That evening he was already almost convinced of the motion of the new star,\" published in ''Studies of Pallas in the Early Nineteenth Century: Historical Studies in Asteroid Research'' by Clifford J. Cunningham (Springer, 2016), page 271.\\n",
